  "prompt": "How early can you check in at the airport for international flight?",
  "response": "For international flights, airlines typically allow passengers to check in as early as 3 hours before the scheduled departure time. Some airlines may even open check-in up to 24 hours in advance online, allowing you to secure your boarding pass before arriving at the airport. However, it's a good idea to check with your specific airline for their exact policies, as they can vary. Additionally, arriving too early may not be practical due to security and airport operations, so aiming for the 3-hour window is usually recommended.",
